### Impact analysis – Please briefly explain who can exploit the vulnerability, and what they gain when doing so

Anyone who can control the benchmark `id` used in a benchpress run can exploit this issue.

Successful exploitation lets the attacker write the generated benchmark JSON report outside the configured report directory to an attacker-chosen relative path. In practical terms, a CI or benchmark automation job that expects output only under `benchpress-reports/` can instead be made to create or overwrite writable files in sibling directories such as `release-artifacts/`.


